1 Download Ubuntu Server ISO
x86_64=https://ubuntu.com/download/server
ARM64=https://ubuntu.com/download/server/arm
IBM POWER=https://ubuntu.com/download/server/power
s390x=https://ubuntu.com/download/server/s390x
RISC-V=https://ubuntu.com/download/risc-v/canonical-built

2 Flash the iso file
3 Setup Ubuntu Server
4 After Finish Reboot
5 run sudo apt update
6 run sudo nano /etc/default/grub
   (If You Need it) Change
    GRUB_TIMEOUT=0 To GRUB_TIMEOUT=5 Then GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=hidden to GRUB_TIMEOUT_STYLE=menu
    then Change GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR=`( . /etc/os-release; echo ${NAME:-Ubuntu} ) 2>/dev/null || echo Ubuntu` to GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR=`( . /etc/os-release; echo ${NAME:-Syslack Linux} ) 2>/dev/null || echo Syslack Linux`
    Ctrl X Y Enter Then sudo update-grub
7 Run sudo nano /etc/os-release
   Then change PREETY_NAME="LTSVERSION LTS" To PREETY_NAME="Syslack Linux"
   Change NAME="Ubuntu" To NAME="Syslack Linux"
   Change VERSION="26.04 LTS (Resolute Racoon)" To VERSION="1.1" VERSION_ID="26.04" To VERSION_ID="1.1"
   Change VERSION_CODENAME=noble To VERSION_CODENAME=viprin
   Change ID=ubuntu to ID=syslack
   Change HOME_URL="https://ubuntu.com/" To HOME_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Syslack-Linux"
   Change SUPPORT_URL="https://help.ubuntu.com/" To SUPPORT_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Syslack-Linux/discussions/2"
   Change BUG_REPORT_URL="https://bugs.launchpad.net/ubuntu/" To BUG_REPORT_URL="https://github.com/Haikal02-alt/Syslack-Linux/issues/3"
   Remove PRIVACY_POLICY_URL
   Remove UBUNTU_CODENAME=noble 
8 Change Some Ubuntu To Syslack On /etc/issue on sudo nano /etc/issue If You See Ubuntu LTSVERSION LTS \n \1 Change it To Syslack Linux \n \1
   Also run sudo nano /etc/issue.net Then Change Ubuntu LTSVERSION LTS To Syslack Linux
   Then Reboot Again sudo reboot
9 Adjust GRUB Scripts
   Run sudo nano /etc/grub.d/10_linux
   If You See if [ "x${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}" = "x" ] ; then
   OS=GNU/Linux
   And OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR} GNU/Linux" 
   Change it To
   if [ "x${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}" = "x" ] ; then
   OS=
   And
   OS="${GRUB_DISTRIBUTOR}"
   Then Find GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU
   Then Disable GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU By Changing GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="true" to GRUB_DISABLE_SUBMENU="false"
   Then sudo update-grub
   Then Reboot Again using sudo reboot
